                            <comment id="13287838" author="enis" created="Sat, 2 Jun 2012 02:42:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the problem is that the master offlines the region at step 3, however, the parent region is recovered, and onlined by RS. So all other region transitions fail for the master. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13287950" author="ram_krish" created="Sat, 2 Jun 2012 14:18:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test case to reproduce this issue.  Infact this will happen in 0.92.0 and 0.92.1 and not in the latest code in 0.92 or 0.94.&lt;br/&gt;
Now the current code &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rs.isSplit() || rs.isSplitting()) {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;does not have this line.  So it should not create a problem here.  It was removed as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6070&quot; title=&quot;AM.nodeDeleted and SSH races creating problems for regions under SPLIT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6070&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6070&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Prior to this it could have happened.  The same has been reproduced in the testcase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13288994" author="devaraj" created="Mon, 4 Jun 2012 23:41:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Ramkrishna. Yeah that should solve the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
